You said:
one script unfortunately python is not installed (risks 10 demerits) it have to a baah script
ChatGPT said:
😤 Ten demerits, Christopher. But you did catch the Intel RST trap, so I’ll waive half for valor in the field. Here's your one-stop Bash script to:

Wipe both disks

Partition for UEFI + Btrfs RAID1

Format EFI as FAT32

Format Btrfs RAID1 across sda2 and sdb1

Create subvolumes

Mount everything ready for OS install

This assumes:

/dev/sda and /dev/sdb are the 1.8TB drives

You want 512MiB EFI + the rest Btrfs on each

System is already booted in UEFI mode (via live ISO or rescue)

⚠️ Danger Close: This will ERASE both drives. Triple-check device names.
#!/bin/bash
set -euo pipefail

# Devices
DISK1="/dev/sda"
DISK2="/dev/sdb"

echo ">>> Wiping existing metadata..."
wipefs -a "$DISK1"
wipefs -a "$DISK2"

echo ">>> Partitioning $DISK1 and $DISK2..."
parted -s "$DISK1" mklabel gpt
parted -s "$DISK1" mkpart ESP fat32 1MiB 513MiB
parted -s "$DISK1" set 1 esp on
parted -s "$DISK1" mkpart primary btrfs 513MiB 100%

parted -s "$DISK2" mklabel gpt
parted -s "$DISK2" mkpart primary btrfs 1MiB 100%

echo ">>> Formatting EFI partition..."
mkfs.fat -F32 "${DISK1}1"

echo ">>> Creating Btrfs RAID1 filesystem..."
mkfs.btrfs -f -m raid1 -d raid1 "${DISK1}2" "${DISK2}1"

echo ">>> Mounting Btrfs root..."
mount "${DISK1}2" /mnt

echo ">>> Creating Btrfs subvolumes..."
btrfs subvolume create /mnt/@
btrfs subvolume create /mnt/@home
btrfs subvolume create /mnt/@var
btrfs subvolume create /mnt/@log
btrfs subvolume create /mnt/@snapshots

echo ">>> Unmounting and remounting with subvols..."
umount /mnt
mount -o subvol=@ "${DISK1}2" /mnt

mkdir -p /mnt/{boot/efi,home,var,log,.snapshots}
mount -o subvol=@home "${DISK1}2" /mnt/home
mount -o subvol=@var "${DISK1}2" /mnt/var
mount -o subvol=@log "${DISK1}2" /mnt/log
mount -o subvol=@snapshots "${DISK1}2" /mnt/.snapshots

mount "${DISK1}1" /mnt/boot/efi

echo ">>> Done. Ready for OS installation on real Btrfs RAID1."
✅ Next Steps After This Script
debootstrap or OS install to /mnt

grub-install --target=x86_64-efi --efi-directory=/boot/efi --bootloader-id=GRUB

Also install GRUB to second EFI if needed: grub-install --removable --efi-directory=/mnt/boot/efi --bootloader-id=GRUB2

Configure /etc/fstab using UUID= entries (blkid is your friend)

Let me know if you want:

Extra flags (like compress=zstd)

A backup copy on Hera

An undo switch if RST rears its head again

Fire when ready, Captain. Athena awaits rebirth.

