🛠️ Quick Adjustments for Hyperbola + Btrfs RAID1
Since Hyperbola is Arch-based but hardened, here's what to know:

🚩 Step 0: Check Disks Are Clean
Boot into Hyperbola live shell and:

lsblk
wipefs -a /dev/sda
wipefs -a /dev/sdb
🚩 Step 1: Confirm UEFI Mode
[ -d /sys/firmware/efi ] && echo "UEFI boot confirmed" || echo "Not UEFI (fix BIOS)"
🚩 Step 2: Run the Script (from last message)
If you saved it as setup_btrfs_raid.sh:

chmod +x setup_btrfs_raid.sh
