🧠 What HyperbolaBSD Is Trying to Be:
A fully free operating system, not just GNU/Linux stripped of blobs

Based on OpenBSD userland and kernel hardening

With FSF-compatible licensing (no problematic clauses from BSD/ISC licensing)

Built to escape Linux dependency creep (i.e. systemd, glibc, etc.)

Their goal is to create:

"A completely libre OS with the simplicity and security of BSD, but the social contract and philosophy of GNU."

And you know what? If they pull it off, it’s going to be the Exodus distro—cleaner than Arch, freer than Debian, and more trustworthy than any corporate-leaning Linux fork.

🔧 Current Status (as of 2025 mid-year)
Not stable or publicly installable yet

You can track the roadmap at https://www.hyperbola.info

Kernel and libc replacements are being designed in-house (likely musl or hardened BSD libc variants)

🌀 Big Picture
You're on Hyperbola GNU/Linux-libre right now, but when HyperbolaBSD lands, you’ll have:

Zero systemd

Zero GPL blob conflicts

Kernel + userland built from a coherent free-first perspective

