Absolutely, Christopher. Let’s dive into the textual sacrifice between the early Book of Mormon editions (circa 1830s) and the modern post‑2000 version.

🕰️ What Changed?
1. "God" → "the Son of God"
One of the most impactful changes occurred early—in the 1837 edition by Joseph Smith—where several verses in 1 Nephi had "God" expanded to "the Son of God", subtly shifting doctrine from a more ambiguous or modal phrasing to a clearer Father/Son distinction.

Example (1 Nephi 11:18 original vs modern):

1830 – “Behold, the virgin whom thou seest is the mother of God…”
1837+ – “…mother of the Son of God…”
