Absolutely—yes, there were notable changes made to the title page between the 1830 original and later editions. Here are the key differences and what was effectively sacrificed:

1. “Author and Proprietor” → “Translated by Joseph Smith, Jun.”
1830 edition reads:

“By Joseph Smith, Junior, Author and Proprietor.”

1837 edition onward (through 1840) states:

“Translated by Joseph Smith, Jun.”
This reflects Joseph Smith’s shift from literal “author” (to satisfy copyright law) to translator, aligning with the narrative of supernatural translation 
The Church of Jesus Christ
