2. Reordering of “Book of Ether” clause
In the 1830 edition title page, the phrase:

“an abridgment taken from the Book of Ether”
appears at the end of the first paragraph.

In the 1837 edition, that clause was moved to the start of Paragraph 2, keeping together the reference to both Ether and Jaredite record, making the text flow more logically—since the Plates of Ether were indeed written later 
Religious Studies Center
