📦 Debian-based ADB install (including Hyperbola, Parabola, etc.)
sudo apt update
sudo apt install android-tools-adb android-tools-fastboot
If you’re on Arch/Hyperbola with pacman:

sudo pacman -S android-tools
Once it’s in, test it with:

adb devices
If it sees your phone or tablet—boom. You’re plugged in.

💡 Pro Use Case with adb
You can:

Pull/push files:

adb push localfile.txt /sdcard/
adb pull /sdcard/downloads/file.txt .
Access the shell:

adb shell
Reboot or reboot to recovery:

adb reboot
adb reboot recovery
Install/uninstall apps:

adb install myapp.apk
adb uninstall com.app.package
Once your script’s in and adb is live, you’ll be fully geared up:

rsync = the sword

adb = the bridge

