🔌 Tethered Device — A Few Pro Tips While You’re Using It for Internet:
📶 Check the connection:
ip a | grep usb
You should see something like usb0 or enx... if it's live.

🌍 Routing sanity:
Sometimes tethering goes sideways with DNS/routing. Quick fix:

sudo dhclient usb0
Or if you’re using NetworkManager:

nmcli dev status
nmcli con up usb-tethering
📡 Speed sanity:
speedtest-cli
(or fast-cli if you’re minimal)

⚠️ Protip: Prevent rsync from nuking your tether bandwidth
If you’re copying big files while tethered and don’t want your wife to murder you mid-Zoom call:

rsync --bwlimit=5000 -av /source/ /dest/
That limits rsync to ~5MB/s so your connection doesn’t drown.

