🔧 Revised LVM Layout (Atlas/Athena-style, Root-Focused)
Mount Point	Size	Notes
/	100G	System, updates, no drama
/home	64G	Your files, config madness
/var	20G	Logs, package cache, DBs
/tmp	4G	Ephemeral junkyard
/srv	16G	Services, experiments
/opt	16G	Optional apps
/usr	32G	Static OS stuff
swap	8G	Legacy safety net
vault	64G	Optional /home/vtrust, encrypted or hidden
Free	Whatever’s left	Leave unallocated for future LVs or snapshots
💥 Commands
lvcreate -L 100G -n lv_root athena_vg
lvcreate -L 64G  -n lv_home athena_vg
lvcreate -L 20G  -n lv_var athena_vg
lvcreate -L 4G   -n lv_tmp athena_vg
lvcreate -L 16G  -n lv_srv athena_vg
lvcreate -L 16G  -n lv_opt athena_vg
lvcreate -L 32G  -n lv_usr athena_vg
lvcreate -L 8G   -n lv_swap athena_vg
lvcreate -L 64G  -n lv_vtrust athena_vg  # encrypted optional
You still get LVM flexibility—you can resize these in-flight or snapshot them like a ninja.

🔐 Optional Vault Mode
cryptsetup luksFormat /dev/athena_vg/lv_vtrust
cryptsetup open /dev/athena_vg/lv_vtrust vtrust_crypt
mkfs.ext4 /dev/mapper/vtrust_crypt
mkdir /mnt/home/vtrust
mount /dev/mapper/vtrust_crypt /mnt/home/vtrust
Add this to /etc/crypttab + /etc/fstab if you want it to mount at boot with a keyfile or passphrase.

Let me know if you want this wrapped into a self-running installer script for Athena/Hera clones—or burned into a backup .sh file for recovery ops.

