ChatGPT said:
Hell yes—2 drives, 2TB of raw power. Let’s engineer this clean and scalable.

You’ve got:

Two 1.8TB drives (let’s say /dev/sdb and /dev/sdc)

You want to use both together under LVM

And dedicate a chunk to /home/nfs (shared storage or networked)

🔧 Plan: Unified 2-Drive LVM Layout (with Room for NFS and Root Muscle)
💡 Strategy:
LVM across both drives (combine into one big volume group)

Break out logical volumes with room for:

/ (root) = 100G

/home = 200G

/home/nfs = 1TB (or more)

/var, /opt, /srv, /tmp, /usr, swap, and optional vault = balance

🛠️ Step-by-Step Commands
1. Partition Both Drives
parted /dev/sdb -- mklabel gpt
parted /dev/sdb -- mkpart primary 0% 100%
parted /dev/sdc -- mklabel gpt
parted /dev/sdc -- mkpart primary 0% 100%
2. Init Physical Volumes
pvcreate /dev/sdb1
pvcreate /dev/sdc1
3. Create One Unified Volume Group
vgcreate athena_vg /dev/sdb1 /dev/sdc1
You now have ~3.6TB of flexible space to play with (minus LVM overhead).

📐 Suggested LV Layout
Mount Point	Size	Notes
/	100G	Big root, no hassle
/home	200G	Userland, configs, personal files
/home/nfs	1.2TB	NFS tree, media, shared
/var	20G	Logs, apt cache
/tmp	4G	Temp junk
/srv	20G	Web, containers, services
/opt	20G	Extra software
/usr	32G	System libraries
swap	8G	If needed
/home/vtrust	64G	Encrypted vault (optional)
Free	~900G	Leave unallocated, LVM lets us grow/shrink later ✔️
4. Create Logical Volumes
lvcreate -L 100G  -n lv_root athena_vg
lvcreate -L 200G  -n lv_home athena_vg
lvcreate -L 1200G -n lv_nfs athena_vg
lvcreate -L 20G   -n lv_var athena_vg
lvcreate -L 4G    -n lv_tmp athena_vg
lvcreate -L 20G   -n lv_srv athena_vg
lvcreate -L 20G   -n lv_opt athena_vg
lvcreate -L 32G   -n lv_usr athena_vg
lvcreate -L 8G    -n lv_swap athena_vg
lvcreate -L 64G   -n lv_vtrust athena_vg
5. Format + Mount
mkfs.ext4 /dev/athena_vg/lv_root
mkfs.ext4 /dev/athena_vg/lv_home
mkfs.ext4 /dev/athena_vg/lv_nfs
mkfs.ext4 /dev/athena_vg/lv_var
mkfs.ext4 /dev/athena_vg/lv_tmp
mkfs.ext4 /dev/athena_vg/lv_srv
mkfs.ext4 /dev/athena_vg/lv_opt
mkfs.ext4 /dev/athena_vg/lv_usr
mkswap     /dev/athena_vg/lv_swap
Mounting:

mount /dev/athena_vg/lv_root /mnt

mkdir -p /mnt/{home,var,tmp,srv,opt,usr,home/nfs,home/vtrust}
mount /dev/athena_vg/lv_home /mnt/home
mount /dev/athena_vg/lv_nfs  /mnt/home/nfs
mount /dev/athena_vg/lv_var  /mnt/var
mount /dev/athena_vg/lv_tmp  /mnt/tmp
mount /dev/athena_vg/lv_srv  /mnt/srv
mount /dev/athena_vg/lv_opt  /mnt/opt
mount /dev/athena_vg/lv_usr  /mnt/usr
swapon /dev/athena_vg/lv_swap
Optional vault:

cryptsetup luksFormat /dev/athena_vg/lv_vtrust
cryptsetup open /dev/athena_vg/lv_vtrust vtrust_crypt
mkfs.ext4 /dev/mapper/vtrust_crypt
mount /dev/mapper/vtrust_crypt /mnt/home/vtrust
🔐 Bonus: Make /home/nfs Exportable
When you're ready for nfs-kernel-server:

echo "/home/nfs 10.3.1.0/24(rw,sync,no_subtree_check)" >> /etc/exports
exportfs -ra
systemctl restart nfs-server
