The chat export contains embedded math, probably in:

LaTeX-like notation (e.g., \int, \frac{}, ∂, etc.)

Unicode math symbols (∆ ∇ ∞ ⊕ ⊗ ∂ ℝ etc.)

If your viewer app (like a plain text viewer or PDF reader) can’t properly render these fonts, you’ll see boxes, blank squares, or strange triangles.

✅ Fixes (Choose based on your OS):
1. Install Nerd Fonts or Math Fonts
If you're on Linux/Debian:

sudo apt install fonts-symbola fonts-noto fonts-noto-mono fonts-dejavu fonts-STIX
